\pard\f0\fs22 Architecture explanation\par
\pard\f0\fs22 Frontend/API Client is the user-facing layer. It sends the prompt to the backend.\par
\pard\f0\fs22 FastAPI endpoint validates the request and decides which runner function should handle it.\par
\pard\f0\fs22 Runner Agent is the execution layer. It starts trace capture and calls each specialist step in order.\par
\pard\f0\fs22 Orchestrator Agent is the routing and final-formatting layer. It decides the flow and prepares the final response.\par
\pard\f0\fs22 Analyst Agent is the data-understanding layer. It reads usage, solar, device, and billing data.\par
\pard\f0\fs22 Advisor Agent is the recommendation layer. It converts analysis into actions the user can follow.\par
\pard\f0\fs22 comments.py supports the whole architecture by storing names, prompts, and ENERGY_AGENT_LOOP.\par
\pard\f0\fs22 AgentResponse is the output layer. It returns answer, tool_calls, and agent_loop to the frontend.\par
